## Logging & Observability

### Log Levels

| Level | Use Case |
|-------|----------|
| **DEBUG** | Development debugging, detailed request/response |
| **INFO** | Normal operations, sync completions, user actions |
| **WARNING** | Rate limits approaching, retryable failures |
| **ERROR** | Exception caught, integration failures |
| **CRITICAL** | System outage, data corruption |

### Log Categories

| Category | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `django` | Framework-level logs |
| `apps` | Application business logic |
| `audit` | Compliance and security events |
| `github_integration` | GitHub API calls and webhooks |
| `celery` | Background task execution |

### Audit Log Fields

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| correlation_id | Unique ID for request tracing |
| user_id | Authenticated user identifier |
| method | HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) |
| path | Request URL path |
| status_code | HTTP response status |
| duration_ms | Request processing time |
| ip | Client IP address |
| user_agent | Client browser/application |

## Background Jobs & Async Processing

### Celery Task Queue Architecture

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **Celery Worker** | Executes background tasks |
| **Redis Broker** | Stores task queue messages |
| **Celery Beat** | Schedules recurring tasks |
| **Flower** | Monitoring dashboard |

### Task Categories

| Category | Examples | Priority |
|----------|----------|----------|
| **GitHub Sync** | Commit sync, PR sync, user mapping | High |
| **AI Processing** | Draft generation, bias detection | Medium |
| **Notifications** | Email alerts, WebSocket pushes | Low |
| **Reports** | CSV export, PDF generation | Low |
| **Cleanup** | Log rotation, cache invalidation | Lowest |

### Scheduled Jobs

| Job Name | Schedule | Purpose |
|----------|----------|---------|
| GitHub Daily Sync | 2:00 AM daily | Full repository sync |
| GitHub Hourly Sync | Every hour | Incremental commit sync |
| Calibration Scan | 9:00 AM daily | Detect bias and outliers |
| Anomaly Detection | 12:30 AM daily | Performance trend analysis |
| Audit Log Cleanup | 1st of month | Archive old logs |

### Retry Strategy

| Attempt | Delay | Action |
|---------|-------|--------|
| 1st | 60 seconds | Retry failed task |
| 2nd | 120 seconds | Retry with exponential backoff |
| 3rd | 240 seconds | Final retry |
| After 3 failures | N/A | Mark as failed, log error, alert admin |

## Coding Standards

### Style Guide

| Standard | Tool | Configuration |
|----------|------|---------------|
| **Code Formatter** | Black | Line length: 100 |
| **Import Sorting** | isort | Profile: black |
| **Linting** | flake8 | Ignore: E501, W503 |
| **Type Checking** | mypy | Strict mode: False |
| **Docstrings** | Google style | Required for public methods |

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Modules | snake_case | `appraisal_service.py` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `AppraisalService` |
| Functions | snake_case | `calculate_rating()` |
| Variables | snake_case | `employee_id` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
| Private methods | _leading_underscore | `_validate_data()` |

