## Dependency Injection Approach

Django doesn't have built-in DI, so we use a combination of patterns:

### Pattern 1: Constructor Injection

Services are instantiated in view constructors, making dependencies explicit and testable.

### Pattern 2: Service Layer with Repository Pattern

Repositories are injected into services, allowing easy mocking for unit tests.

### Pattern 3: Factory Functions

Simple factory functions create service instances with their dependencies.

### Pattern 4: Django App Registry

Services can be registered and retrieved via Django's app registry for cross-app dependencies.

### Dependency Rules

| Rule | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Views → Services | Views depend only on services |
| Services → Repositories | Services depend only on repositories |
| Repositories → Models | Repositories depend only on models |
| No circular dependencies | Services cannot depend on each other cyclically |
| Single responsibility | Each class has one reason to change |

## GitHub External Integration Details

### Connection Credentials

| Credential | Source | Purpose |
|------------|--------|---------|
| `GITHUB_API_URL` | Environment | GitHub API endpoint |
| `GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` | Environment | Authentication for API calls |
| `GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | Environment | HMAC verification for webhooks |
| `GITHUB_APP_ID` | GitHub App Settings | GitHub App authentication |
| `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY` | GitHub App Settings | JWT signing for GitHub App |
| `GITHUB_INSTALLATION_ID` | GitHub App Settings | Installation-specific token |

### Webhook Endpoint

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **URL** | `POST https://api.yourcompany.com/api/v1/webhooks/github/` |
| **Secret** | Configured in GitHub repository settings |
| **Events** | push, pull_request, pull_request_review |

### API Rate Limits

| Authentication | Rate Limit | Reset Strategy |
|----------------|------------|----------------|
| Personal Access Token | 5,000 req/hour | Cache tokens, queue requests |
| GitHub App | 15,000 req/hour | Distributed across installations |

### Data Collected for Appraisal

| Data Type | GitHub API Endpoint | Usage in Appraisal |
|-----------|---------------------|---------------------|
| Commits | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/commits` | Activity metric, code contribution |
| Pull Requests | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls` | Collaboration, code review |
| Code Reviews | `GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/reviews` | Quality, mentorship |
| User Info | `GET /users/{username}` | Identity mapping |

